We are going to discuss about IoT, the Internet Of Things. 
The Internet of Things (IoT) refers to a network The Internet of 
Things (IoT) refers to a network of physical devices, vehicles, buildings, and 
other items embedded with electronics, sensors, software, and network 
connectivity, which allows them to collect and exchange data. The data collected 
from IoT devices can be analyzed to gain insights into user behavior, improve 
operations, and enable new applications and services. IoT has many potential 
applications across various industries, including healthcare, manufacturing, 
agriculture, transportation, and more. However, the proliferation of IoT devices 
also raises concerns about privacy, security, and data ownership. And this is to end what I just pasted. 

